      "content": "ok, that's a good start. focusing on the \"racial stability\" and \"property rights\" points... can you expand on the \"racial stability\" argument? like, what was the actual logic used to say that segregation actually prevented conflict? i want to see if i can understand the specific sociological or \"order-based\" arguments they used to make it sound like a logical policy rather than just hate.",
